cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper discusses feature detectors and descriptors for computer vision tasks, specifically focusing on keypoint detection and image retrieval. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments and comparison of different methods could also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
